	New Delhi: Archrivals India and Pakistan were Tuesday clubbed in the same pool B for the 2010 hockey World Cup. Defending champions Germany and Australia got the top billing for the meet. Pool B also has Australia, Spain, England and South Africa. Pool A, apart from Germany, comprises the Netherlands, Korea, New Zealand, Canada and Argentina. The tournament will be held in New Delhi from Feb.28 to March 13.        
	Khanty Mansiysk (Russia): Top seed GM Boris Gelfand of Israel won the Chess World Cup, defeating former world champion Ruslan Ponomariov of Ukraine in a tiebreaker.       
	Racial abuse  
	Karachi: The PCB Tuesday played down the incident of racial abuse of the Pakistan national players in New Zealand during the third Test in Napier, saying there was nothing to complain about. Reports quoted a spectator as saying that a group inside the stadium abused the visiting cricketers, calling them Pakistani terrorists.  
